Description: üè∞ Your Last Line of Defense - Application Firewall for Linux
 Bastion Firewall is an outbound application firewall built specifically for
 Zorin OS 18 (and compatible with all Debian-based distributions). Like a
 medieval bastion protecting a fortress, Bastion stands guard over your
 system's network connections.
 .
 Features:
  - Real-time packet interception using netfilter
  - Beautiful GUI dialogs for permission requests
  - Independent tray icon with visual status indicators
  - Security hardened (5-phase implementation, score: 2/10 LOW RISK)
  - Per-application, per-port rules
  - UFW integration for complete firewall coverage
  - Control panel for managing settings and rules
  - Auto-start support with systemctl controls
 .
 The installer will guide you through the setup process and can automatically
 configure UFW and start the firewall service.
Homepage: https://github.com/bastion-firewall/bastion-firewall
